      <!-- Pathway -->

      <hr class="govuk-section-break govuk-section-break--m govuk-section-break">

      <p class="govuk-body">This service is called 'Get funding to improve animal health and welfare'. It forms part of the Animal Health and Welfare Pathway. It's designed to help farmers:</p>
        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
          <li>test for endemic diseases and conditions</li>
          <li>increase animal productivity</li>
          <li>improve animal welfare</li>
        </ul>

      <p class="govuk-body">There are 2 parts to the service:</p>
        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
          <li>animal health and welfare review</li>
          <li>endemic disease follow-up</li>
        </ul>
      </p>

      <p class="govuk-body">
        A follow-up can only be done after a review and on the same species as the review. For the farmer to be eligible to claim funding, they must follow the timing rules. To help the farmer follow the timing rules, you can read more about <a href="#">timing of reviews</a> and <a href="#">timing of follow-ups</a>.
      </p>

      <p class="govuk-body">
        Reviews and follow-ups are not inspections or audits.
      </p>

