      <!-- Who can take part -->

      <h2 id="what-you-could-get" class="govuk-heading-m">
        Who can take part
      </h2>
      <p class="govuk-body">
        A farmer is eligible if they keep any of the following per herd or flock:
        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
          <li>11 or more beef cattle</li>
          <li>11 or more dairy cattle</li>
          <li>51 or more pigs</li>
          <li>21 or more sheep</li>
        </ul>
      </p>

      <!-- Arrange a review or follow-up  -->

      <h2 id="what-you-could-get" class="govuk-heading-m">
        Arrange a review or follow-up 
      </h2>

      <p class="govuk-body">
        The farmer will contact you to arrange a review or follow-up. 
      </p>
      
      <p class="govuk-body">
        Review and follow-ups do not have a set time, but they typically take between 2 and 3 hours.
      </p>

      <p class="govuk-body">
        The farmer can agree with you to do a review or follow-up either:
        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
          <li>over several visits to the farm</li>
          <li>in a single visit</li>
        </ul>
      </p>

      <!-- What a farmer will ask the vet to do  -->

      <h2 id="what-you-could-get" class="govuk-heading-m">
        What a farmer will ask the vet to do 
      </h2>

      <p class="govuk-body">
        The farmer will ask the vet to follow the steps in the <a href="#">review guidance</a> or <a href="#">follow-up guidance</a>.
      </p>
      
      <!-- Required testing   -->

      <h2 id="what-you-could-get" class="govuk-heading-m">
        Required testing 
      </h2>
      
      <p class="govuk-body">
        The vet guidance has information on:
        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
          <li>testing and specifications a laboratory needs to meet </li>
          <li>what you need to include in a summary and written report</li>
          <li>how to confirm a herd with our 'Tell us about a herd or flock' section of the form</li>
        </ul>
      </p>

      <p class="govuk-body">
        Read vet guidance for:</p>
      <ul class="govuk-list">
        <li>
          <a class="govuk-link" href="#">Cattle</a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a class="govuk-link" href="#">Pigs</a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a class="govuk-link" href="#">Sheep</a>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <!-- Vet templates   -->

      <h2 id="what-you-could-get" class="govuk-heading-m">
        Vet templates 
      </h2>

      <p class="govuk-body">
        There are vet templates your vet can use to:</p>
      <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
        <li>Provide the information about the visit, so you can make a claim</li>
        <li>Confirm the herd that they did the visit for</li>
      </ul>
      
      <p class="govuk-body">
        <a href="guidance-vet-download">
        Vet summary templates for all species
        </a>
      </p>

      <h3 id="what-you-could-get" class="govuk-heading-m">
        Other schemes
      </h2>

      <p class="govuk-body">
        The farmer cannot use other accreditation scheme test results for this funding.
      </p>

      <p class="govuk-body">
        They can use the review or follow-up test results for other accreditation schemes they're a member of. They should also check with the accreditation scheme that they'll accept testing from the review or follow-up.
      </p>

